      "slug": "tin-ingot",
      "title": "Tin Ingot",
      "category": "Items/Resources & Materials/Ingots",
      "source": "Items/Resources & Materials/Ingots/Tin Ingot.md",
      "content": "---\ntags:\n  - Metal\nItem Class: Common\nMaterial Type: Metal\nMaterial Form: Ingot\nSource: Tin Ore\nWeight: 0.9kg\nWeight Class: Light\nDurability: Low\nEnchantment Affinity: 10% (+0 dice)\nMarket Value: 4 Marks\n---\n\n\n## Effect\nA refined but weak metal, Tin Ingots are primarily used as a stabilising component in alloy crafting rather than for direct equipment creation.\n\n---\n\n## Crafting Use\n- Core component for Bronze\n- Used in beginner alloy recipes\n\n---\n\n## Material Traits\n- Very soft and flexible  \n- Cannot hold an edge  \n- Supports alloy integrity  \n\n---\n\n## Alloy Use\n- [[Bronze Ingot]]\n\n---\n\n## Enchantment Use\n- Enhances enchantment stability in alloys  \n- Reduces magical backlash  \n\n---\n\n## Crafting Source\n- Requires: 4x [[Tin Ore]]\n\n---\n\n## Quote\n*\"Strength is not always found in the metal itself, but in what it allows.\"*"
