      "source": "Items/Resources & Materials/Ores/Common Ores/Gold Ore.md",
      "content": "---\ntags:\n  - Metal\nItem Class: Common\nMaterial Type: Metal\nMaterial Form: Ore\nRefines Into: Gold Ingot\nRefinement Ratio: 4:1\nWeight Class: Medium\nDurability: Low\nEnchantment Affinity: 35% (+3 dice)\nMarket Value: 10 Marks\n---\n\n\n## Effect\nGold Ore is rich in magical conductivity, making it one of the most valuable materials for enchantment despite its softness.\n\n---\n\n## Lore\nKnown as the *“Tears of the Dawn,”* gold is believed to be crystallised sunlight buried within the earth.\n\n---\n\n## Material & Crafting Traits\n- Rare and valuable  \n- Soft and easily refined  \n- Highly magical  \n\n---\n\n## Refinement\n- Smelts into: [[Gold Ingot]]\n- Ratio: 4 Ore → 1 Ingot\n\n---\n\n## Alloy Use\n- [[Sunsteel]] (future)\n- Reinforcement alloys\n\n---\n\n## Enchantment Use\n- Exceptional for divine and celestial magic  \n- Stabilises high-tier enchantments  \n\n---\n\n## Quote\n*\"Gold does not fade — it remembers the light.\"*"
