      "source": "Items/Resources & Materials/Ores/Common Ores/Iron Ore.md",
      "content": "---\ntags:\n  - Metal\nItem Class: Common\nMaterial Type: Metal\nMaterial Form: Ore\nRefines Into: Iron Ingot\nRefinement Ratio: 4:1\nWeight Class: Medium\nDurability: Moderate\nEnchantment Affinity: 10% (+0 dice)\nMarket Value: 3 Marks\n---\n\n\n## Effect\nIron Ore is dense and impurity-rich, requiring proper smelting to unlock its strength. Once refined, it forms the backbone of most weapons and armor.\n\n---\n\n## Lore\nCalled the *“Blood of the World,”* iron runs deep beneath the earth. Civilizations rose and fell by their ability to mine and shape it.\n\n---\n\n## Material & Crafting Traits\n- Dense and widely available  \n- Requires stronger heat to refine  \n- Reliable base material for combat equipment  \n\n---\n\n## Refinement\n- Smelts into: [[Iron Ingot]]\n- Ratio: 4 Ore → 1 Ingot\n- Notes: Requires stable heat for proper refinement\n\n---\n\n## Alloy Use\n- [[Steel Ingot]]\n\n---\n\n## Enchantment Use\n- Neutral magical properties  \n- Supports basic rune and enchantment structures  \n\n---\n\n## Quote\n*\"From stone and fire, strength is born.\"*"
