      "title": "Nickel Ore",
      "category": "Items/Resources & Materials/Ores/Common Ores",
      "source": "Items/Resources & Materials/Ores/Common Ores/Nickel Ore.md",
      "content": "---\ntags:\n  - Metal\nItem Class: Common\nMaterial Type: Metal\nMaterial Form: Ore\nRefines Into: Nickel Ingot\nRefinement Ratio: 4:1\nWeight Class: Medium\nDurability: Moderate\nEnchantment Affinity: 10% (+0 dice)\nMarket Value: 3 Marks\n---\n\n\n## Effect\nNickel Ore contains balanced metallic properties that allow it to stabilise and reinforce other materials when refined and alloyed. It is rarely used alone but is essential in improving durability and magical consistency.\n\n---\n\n## Lore\nKnown as the *“Silent Binder,”* nickel was long overlooked until master smiths discovered its ability to unify stronger metals without weakening them. It is said to be the metal that prevents failure before it happens.\n\n---\n\n## Material & Crafting Traits\n- Moderate density and durability  \n- Resistant to corrosion  \n- Stabilises alloy structures  \n- Commonly found near iron deposits  \n\n---\n\n## Refinement\n- Smelts into: [[Nickel Ingot]]\n- Ratio: 4 Ore → 1 Ingot\n- Notes: Stable refinement with low material loss\n\n---\n\n## Alloy Use\n- Reinforcement alloys\n- Stability-focused metals\n\n---\n\n## Enchantment Use\n- Improves enchantment stability  \n- Reduces failure or backlash in enchanted items  \n\n---\n\n## Quote\n*\"It is not seen in the blade — but without it, the blade fails.\"*"
