      "title": "Thorium Ore",
      "category": "Items/Resources & Materials/Ores/Unusual Ores",
      "source": "Items/Resources & Materials/Ores/Unusual Ores/Thorium Ore.md",
      "content": "---\ntags:\n  - Metal\nItem Class: Unusual\nMaterial Type: Metal\nMaterial Form: Ore\nRefines Into: Thorium Ingot\nRefinement Ratio: 4:1\nWeight Class: Medium-Heavy\nDurability: Very High\nEnchantment Affinity: 40% (+3 dice)\nMarket Value: 15 Marks\n---\n## Effect\nThorium Ore radiates stored arcane energy, making it highly reactive during refinement. When properly processed, it produces a metal capable of storing and releasing magical power.\n\n---\n\n## Lore\nForged in the deep veins of the world where lightning once struck the earth’s core, thorium is known as the *“Metal of Living Light.”* It is both revered and feared for its raw power.\n\n---\n\n## Material & Crafting Traits\n- Emits low levels of magical radiation  \n- Extremely dense and heat-resistant  \n- Difficult to mine and handle safely  \n- Requires skilled refinement to stabilise  \n\n---\n\n## Refinement\n- Smelts into: [[Thorium Ingot]]\n- Ratio: 4 Ore → 1 Ingot\n- Notes: Requires controlled environment to prevent instability\n\n---\n\n## Alloy Use\n- High-tier magical alloys (future)\n\n---\n\n## Enchantment Use\n- Strong affinity with Radiant and Arcane magic  \n- Stores residual magical energy  \n\n---\n\n## Quote\n*\"Power sleeps in its veins — waiting to be awakened.\"*"
